<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="111" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,580,715]" pageId="1" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,289,580,606]" pageId="1" pageNumber="111">Diagnosis:—</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="H. S. Lo" authorityName="H. S. Lo" box="[589,928,580,606]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="1" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="petrophila">
<emphasis box="[589,836,580,606]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="111">Spiradiclis petrophila</emphasis>
H.S.Lo
</taxonomicName>
(1983: 30, 33) for having tubular, white and shorter than 
<quantity box="[277,342,616,643]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="111" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
corollas, but differs from the latter mainly by the persistent, ovate to ovate-oblong, 
<quantity box="[1287,1395,616,643]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="111" unit="mm" value="8.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="7.0">7–10 mm</quantity>
long (vs. caducous, triangular, 
<quantity box="[420,533,652,679]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="111" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2 mm</quantity>
long) stipules, and white or sometimes pink, oblong to ovate-oblong, 
<quantity box="[1304,1396,652,679]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="111" unit="mm" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5 mm</quantity>
long (vs. green, narrowly triangular, 
<quantity box="[490,625,688,715]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="111" unit="mm" value="0.55" valueMax="0.8" valueMin="0.3">0.3–0.8 mm</quantity>
long) bracts.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
