<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,158,833]" pageId="3" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,516,662,688]" pageId="3" pageNumber="113">Taxonomic relationships:—</emphasis>
According to the classification of 
<bibRefCitation author="Lo, H. S." box="[887,999,662,689]" pageId="3" pageNumber="113" pagination="275 - 283" refId="ref2494" refString="Lo, H. S. (1998) Materials for Chinese Rubiaceae (IV). Bulletin of Botanical Research, Harbin 18: 275 - 283." type="journal article" year="1998">Lo (1998)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1008,1226,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="3" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elliptica">
<emphasis box="[1008,1226,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="113">Spiradiclis elliptica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H.S.Lo" authorityYear="1998" box="[136,304,698,724]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Sinospiradiclis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="3" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[136,304,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="113">Sinospiradiclis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the subglobose capsules dehiscent with 4 valves when mature. This species is distinguishable from other species of the genus mainly by its large stipule and distinctive bract. To our knowledge, the bracts of the known species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blume" authorityYear="1926" box="[337,458,770,796]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="3" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[337,458,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="113">Spiradiclis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are described as linear or subulate (vs. oblong to ovate-oblong in 
<taxonomicName box="[1197,1317,770,797]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="3" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elliptica">
<emphasis box="[1197,1317,770,797]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="113">S. elliptica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the apices of which are lanceolate or acute (vs. rounded), and the color are green (vs. white or sometimes pink).
</paragraph>
